EBRD May Invest $1 Billion in Kazakhstan in 2011, Interfax Says

-- B y   N a r i m a n   G i z i t d i n o v
-- 
2011-05-05T10:22:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-05/ebrd-may-invest-1-billion-in-kazakhstan-in-2011-interfax-says.html
The European Bank for Reconstruction
and Development may invest about $1 billion in Kazakh projects
this year, Interfax reported, citing Finance Minister Bolat Zhamishev.  The 2011 financing is part of the 2.8 billion euros ($4.2
billion) the EBRD has allocated for projects throughout the
Kazakh economy in the longer term, Zhamishev said today in
Astana, according to Interfax.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nariman Gizitdinov in Almaty at 
 ngizitdinov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at   sev@bloomberg.net  